type Normalize2<T, K = keyof T> = K extends keyof TThe issue is that when `allowObjectInHTMLChildren` is `true`, the augmentation changes `HTMLAttributes.children` to `ReactI18NextChild | Iterable<ReactI18NextChild>`. When you have multiple JSX children like `{policyEnactments.length} {t('nodes')}`, TypeScript sees them as separate children (an implicit array), and the type checker complains about "expects a single child" because the type is a union, not explicitly `ReactI18NextChild[]`.

